{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Last year I showed these two slides so that"},{"time":3000,"text":"demonstrate that the arctic ice cap,"},{"time":5000,"text":"which for most of the last three million years"},{"time":7000,"text":"has been the size of the lower 48 states,"},{"time":9000,"text":"has shrunk by 40 percent."},{"time":11000,"text":"But this understates the seriousness of this particular problem"},{"time":14000,"text":"because it doesn't show the thickness of the ice."},{"time":17000,"text":"The arctic ice cap is, in a sense,"},{"time":19000,"text":"the beating heart of the global climate system."},{"time":22000,"text":"It expands in winter and contracts in summer."},{"time":25000,"text":"The next slide I show you will be"},{"time":28000,"text":"a rapid fast-forward of what's happened over the last 25 years."},{"time":32000,"text":"The permanent ice is marked in red."},{"time":34000,"text":"As you see, it expands to the dark blue --"},{"time":37000,"text":"that's the annual ice in winter,"},{"time":39000,"text":"and it contracts in summer."},{"time":41000,"text":"The so-called permanent ice, five years old or older,"},{"time":43000,"text":"you can see is almost like blood,"},{"time":46000,"text":"spilling out of the body here."},{"time":50000,"text":"In 25 years it's gone from this, to this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54000,"text":"This is a problem because the warming"},{"time":57000,"text":"heats up the frozen ground around the Arctic Ocean,"},{"time":60000,"text":"where there is a massive amount of frozen carbon"},{"time":63000,"text":"which, when it thaws, is turned into methane by microbes."},{"time":66000,"text":"Compared to the total amount of global warming pollution in the atmosphere,"},{"time":70000,"text":"that amount could double if we cross this tipping point."},{"time":74000,"text":"Already in some shallow lakes in Alaska,"},{"time":77000,"text":"methane is actively bubbling up out of the water."},{"time":79000,"text":"Professor Katey Walter from the University of Alaska"},{"time":82000,"text":"went out with another team to another shallow lake last winter."},{"time":96000,"text":"Video: Whoa! (Laughter)"},{"time":98000,"text":"Al Gore: She's okay. The question is whether we will be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101000,"text":"And one reason is, this enormous heat sink"},{"time":103000,"text":"heats up Greenland from the north."},{"time":106000,"text":"This is an annual melting river."},{"time":109000,"text":"But the volumes are much larger than ever."},{"time":112000,"text":"This is the Kangerlussuaq River in southwest Greenland."},{"time":115000,"text":"If you want to know how sea level rises"},{"time":117000,"text":"from land-base ice melting"},{"time":119000,"text":"this is where it reaches the sea."},{"time":121000,"text":"These flows are increasing very rapidly."},{"time":123000,"text":"At the other end of the planet, Antarctica"},{"time":125000,"text":"the largest mass of ice on the planet."},{"time":127000,"text":"Last month scientists reported the entire continent"},{"time":129000,"text":"is now in negative ice balance."},{"time":131000,"text":"And west Antarctica cropped up on top some under-sea islands,"},{"time":135000,"text":"is particularly rapid in its melting."},{"time":138000,"text":"That's equal to 20 feet of sea level, as is Greenland."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142000,"text":"In the Himalayas, the third largest mass of ice:"},{"time":144000,"text":"at the top you see new lakes, which a few years ago were glaciers."},{"time":148000,"text":"40 percent of all the people in the world"},{"time":150000,"text":"get half of their drinking water from that melting flow."},{"time":152000,"text":"In the Andes, this glacier is the"},{"time":154000,"text":"source of drinking water for this city."},{"time":156000,"text":"The flows have increased."},{"time":158000,"text":"But when they go away, so does much of the drinking water."},{"time":161000,"text":"In California there has been a 40 percent"},{"time":163000,"text":"decline in the Sierra snowpack."},{"time":165000,"text":"This is hitting the reservoirs."},{"time":167000,"text":"And the predictions, as you've read, are serious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170000,"text":"This drying around the world has lead to"},{"time":172000,"text":"a dramatic increase in fires."},{"time":174000,"text":"And the disasters around the world"},{"time":177000,"text":"have been increasing at an absolutely extraordinary"},{"time":179000,"text":"and unprecedented rate."},{"time":181000,"text":"Four times as many in the last 30 years"},{"time":183000,"text":"as in the previous 75."},{"time":185000,"text":"This is a completely unsustainable pattern."},{"time":189000,"text":"If you look at in the context of history"},{"time":192000,"text":"you can see what this is doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197000,"text":"In the last five years"},{"time":199000,"text":"we've added 70 million tons of CO2"},{"time":201000,"text":"every 24 hours --"},{"time":203000,"text":"25 million tons every day to the oceans."},{"time":205000,"text":"Look carefully at the area of the eastern Pacific,"},{"time":208000,"text":"from the Americas, extending westward,"},{"time":210000,"text":"and on either side of the Indian subcontinent,"},{"time":213000,"text":"where there is a radical depletion of oxygen in the oceans."},{"time":217000,"text":"The biggest single cause of global warming,"},{"time":219000,"text":"along with deforestation, which is 20 percent of it, is the burning of fossil fuels."},{"time":223000,"text":"Oil is a problem, and coal is the most serious problem."},{"time":226000,"text":"The United States is one of the two"},{"time":228000,"text":"largest emitters, along with China."},{"time":230000,"text":"And the proposal has been to build a lot more coal plants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"But we're beginning to see a sea change."},{"time":236000,"text":"Here are the ones that have been cancelled in the last few years"},{"time":239000,"text":"with some green alternatives proposed."},{"time":241000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":242000,"text":"However there is a political battle"},{"time":245000,"text":"in our country."},{"time":247000,"text":"And the coal industries and the oil industries"},{"time":249000,"text":"spent a quarter of a billion dollars in the last calendar year"},{"time":252000,"text":"promoting clean coal,"},{"time":254000,"text":"which is an oxymoron."},{"time":256000,"text":"That image reminded me of something."},{"time":258000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":261000,"text":"Around Christmas, in my home in Tennessee,"},{"time":263000,"text":"a billion gallons of coal sludge was spilled."},{"time":266000,"text":"You probably saw it on the news."},{"time":268000,"text":"This, all over the country, is the second largest waste stream in America."},{"time":272000,"text":"This happened around Christmas."},{"time":274000,"text":"One of the coal industry's ads around Christmas was this one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277000,"text":"Video: ♪♫ Frosty the coal man is a jolly, happy soul."},{"time":280000,"text":"He's abundant here in America,"},{"time":282000,"text":"and he helps our economy grow."},{"time":284000,"text":"Frosty the coal man is getting cleaner everyday."},{"time":288000,"text":"He's affordable and adorable, and workers keep their pay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292000,"text":"Al Gore: This is the source of much of the coal in West Virginia."},{"time":296000,"text":"The largest mountaintop miner is the head of Massey Coal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301000,"text":"Video: Don Blankenship: Let me be clear about it. Al Gore,"},{"time":303000,"text":"Nancy Pelosi, Harry Reid, they don't know what they're talking about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307000,"text":"Al Gore: So the Alliance for Climate Protection"},{"time":309000,"text":"has launched two campaigns."},{"time":311000,"text":"This is one of them, part of one of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314000,"text":"Video: Actor: At COALergy we view climate change as a very serious"},{"time":316000,"text":"threat to our business."},{"time":318000,"text":"That's why we've made it our primary goal"},{"time":320000,"text":"to spend a large sum of money"},{"time":322000,"text":"on an advertising effort to help bring out and complicate"},{"time":325000,"text":"the truth about coal."},{"time":327000,"text":"The fact is, coal isn't dirty."},{"time":329000,"text":"We think it's clean --"},{"time":331000,"text":"smells good, too."},{"time":333000,"text":"So don't worry about climate change."},{"time":336000,"text":"Leave that up to us."},{"time":338000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":339000,"text":"Video: Actor: Clean coal -- you've heard a lot about it."},{"time":341000,"text":"So let's take a tour of this state-of-the-art clean coal facility."},{"time":347000,"text":"Amazing! The machinery is kind of loud."},{"time":350000,"text":"But that's the sound of clean coal technology."},{"time":354000,"text":"And while burning coal is one of the leading causes of global warming,"},{"time":357000,"text":"the remarkable clean coal technology you see here"},{"time":360000,"text":"changes everything."},{"time":362000,"text":"Take a good long look: this is today's clean coal technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367000,"text":"Al Gore: Finally, the positive alternative"},{"time":369000,"text":"meshes with our economic challenge"},{"time":371000,"text":"and our national security challenge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"Video: Narrator: America is in crisis -- the economy,"},{"time":375000,"text":"national security, the climate crisis."},{"time":378000,"text":"The thread that links them all:"},{"time":380000,"text":"our addiction to carbon based fuels,"},{"time":382000,"text":"like dirty coal and foreign oil."},{"time":384000,"text":"But now there is a bold new solution to get us out of this mess."},{"time":387000,"text":"Repower America with 100 percent clean electricity"},{"time":390000,"text":"within 10 years."},{"time":392000,"text":"A plan to put America back to work,"},{"time":394000,"text":"make us more secure, and help stop global warming."},{"time":397000,"text":"Finally, a solution that's big enough to solve our problems."},{"time":400000,"text":"Repower America. Find out more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402000,"text":"Al Gore: This is the last one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411000,"text":"Video: Narrator: It's about repowering America."},{"time":413000,"text":"One of the fastest ways to cut our dependence"},{"time":415000,"text":"on old dirty fuels that are killing our planet."},{"time":420000,"text":"Man: Future's over here. Wind, sun, a new energy grid."},{"time":425000,"text":"Man #2: New investments to create high-paying jobs."},{"time":430000,"text":"Narrator: Repower America. It's time to get real."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434000,"text":"Al Gore: There is an old African proverb that says,"},{"time":437000,"text":"\"If you want to go quickly, go alone."},{"time":439000,"text":"If you want to go far, go together.\""},{"time":442000,"text":"We need to go far, quickly."},{"time":444000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":446000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}